# CSS Standards

## Animation
- Animate only `transform` and `opacity` — compositor-friendly
- Never `transition: all` — list each property explicitly
- Height animations: `grid-template-rows: 0fr` to `1fr`, not `height`
- Set correct `transform-origin`
- Honor `prefers-reduced-motion`: crossfade alternative or disable

## Typography
- `font-display: swap` on all @font-face
- `clamp(min, preferred, max)` for fluid headings
- `text-wrap: balance` or `text-pretty` on headings
- `font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums` for number columns
- Ellipsis: `…` not `...`; curly quotes not straight quotes

## Layout
- Flex/grid over JS measurement for layout
- Flex children need `min-width: 0` for text truncation
- `gap` over margin for sibling spacing
- `overflow-x: hidden` on containers to prevent unwanted scrollbars
- Semantic variable names: `--space-sm`, `--text-body` not `--spacing-8`, `--font-16`

## Performance
- `content-visibility: auto` for long off-screen sections
- `<link rel="preconnect">` for CDN/font domains
- Images: explicit width/height to prevent CLS

## Dark Mode
- `color-scheme: dark` on html for dark themes (fixes scrollbar, native inputs)
- Reduce font weight slightly in dark mode (perceived weight is lighter)
- Depth via lighter surfaces, not shadows
- Desaturate accents slightly in dark mode
- Never pure black background — use dark gray (12-18% lightness)

## Interaction
- `touch-action: manipulation` on interactive elements
- `overscroll-behavior: contain` in modals/drawers
- `-webkit-tap-highlight-color` set intentionally
